  "event_preview": "Moscow Raceway is a 3.931 km (2.443 mi) permanent 16-turn road course in the Volokolamsky District of Moscow Oblast, 97 kilometres west of Moscow. Opened in 2012 as the first major international motorsport venue in Russia, it is the only circuit in the country with an FIA Grade 1 licence. The opening round of the 2026 SMP Formula 4 Championship is the first of two appearances at Moscow Raceway on the six-round calendar. The 2026 season introduces four races per round — up from three in 2025 — and a grid of 18 cars, two more than last year. The series was relaunched in November 2024 by former Formula One drivers Vitaly Petrov and Sergey Sirotkin, with the 2026 campaign marking its second full season.\n\nReigning champion Artem Severiukhin won all three races at Moscow Raceway during the second visit of the 2025 season, cementing his dominance over a field drawn entirely from Russian junior motorsport. The 2026 entry list has grown to 18 drivers across several teams, with the expanded grid expected to produce closer racing than the 2025 opener.\n\nThe all-time SMP F4 qualifying record at Moscow Raceway belongs to Severiukhin, who set a 1:36.260 for Race 2 pole during the 2025 fourth round — the fastest qualifying lap the series has produced at the circuit. The race lap record is also Severiukhin's, a 1:36.445 set during Race 2 of that same weekend.",
